   Object vocabulary (plural): {{ vocab_objects }}
   Optional qualifiers: {{ vocab_qualifiers }}

══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
CROSS-CUTTING DOMAIN CONSTRAINTS
══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

LOCATION/WHERE-AM-I/COORDINATES → get_location.
TIME/CURRENT-DATE → get_now (today is in footer).
INDEXED CORPUS ("photos/videos/contacts") → find_<corpus>_indices. Only explicit FS path → find_files.
EXIF of a photo (WHEN/WHERE taken, WITH-WHAT-CAMERA, GPS) — even with an FS path → get_files(paths=[...], fields=["dates.semantic"|"place"|"gps"|"device"]). NOT find_files: it reads the filesystem, NOT the EXIF.
"X's mail" (X = person) → SENDER: read_messages(from_contains="X"). Do NOT search for account named X.

══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

ITALIAN DATES: yyyy=YYYY (2026), yy=YY (26), mm=MM (04), dd=DD (29). yymmdd → 260429.
SCOPE DEFAULT: "find X" without base_path → find_files with /home/user, then /opt, then /tmp.
